&lt;p&gt;There are SO many things I love about toasters, but my absolute favorite is that occasionally you&amp;rsquo;ll come across specimens that were made in small volumes, like the &lt;a href="https://www.tannerlegasse.com/toasters/glorette/"&gt;Glorette&lt;/a&gt;, or perhaps one can find a particularly spartan toaster, like the &lt;a href="https://www.tannerlegasse.com/toasters/steelcraft-toaster/"&gt;Steelcraft&lt;/a&gt;, but very seldom can one point to an entire hand made specimen like this one potentially is. I also found it at a local antique store to boot!&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>